ironment snapshots from the\nsame workspace APIs the app already trusts. If this dependency shape\nbecomes too costly later, it can be replaced behind an agentlog-local snapshot\nadapter without changing the stored turn model.\n\nOne possible storage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key\n[TRUNCATED]\n1 shape is:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"turn_key\": \"sha256-a1b2c3d4e5f60718aabbccddeeff0011\",\n  \"captured_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:42:11.123Z\",\n  \"source_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"capture_kind\": \"incremental\",\n  \"record_count\": 3,\n  \"first_record_index\": 42,\n  \"last_record_index\": 44,\n  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"environment_snapshot_status\": \"complete\"\n}\n```\n\nThe summary lives under a session key, so it does not need to repeat\n`session_key`. `source_key` and the record index bounds are convenience fields\nfor quick timeline rendering and debugging; exact record membership remains in\n`TurnDetail`.\n\n`TurnDetail` is the authoritative observation object. It contains exact record\nmembership plus the environment snapshot and should be stored as a JSON string\nvalue written through `MetaEdit::SetValue`.\n\n## V1 Implementation Checklist\n\n1. Bump the pinned `git-meta-lib` dependency to a revision containing\n   `MetaEdit::SetValue`.\n2. Add turn storage types for `TurnSummary`, `TurnDetail`, record membership,\n   `observed_targets`, and environment snapshot data.\n3. Change capture write flow so dedupe returns the newly accepted transcript\n   records and their ordered record hashes.\n4. Compute `turn_key` from `session_key`, `source_key`, and ordered new record\n   hashes using 128-bit truncated SHA-256.\n5. Add a capture lock or optimistic retry around dedupe, previous-turn lookup,\n   and write.\n6. Find the previous capture turn in the same session and store\n   `previous_turn_key` when available.\n7. Collect the environment snapshot best-effort using shared GitButler workspace\n   APIs and a path-only worktree snapshot helper behind an agentlog-local\n   adapter.\n8. Collect commit file paths with path-only tree comparisons, capped at 256\n   paths per list, and cap commits per branch.\n9. Write session metadata, source metadata, transcript records, record hashes,\n   turn summary, turn detail, and branch/review/change index memberships in one\n   logical GitMeta `apply_edits` batch.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:21:25.813Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}